    "en": {
      "title": "The Parliamentary Home Affairs Committee is reappointed",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Home Affairs Committee of the Parliament, which was abolished with the conclusion of the second session of the Ninth Parliament, was re-appointed today (29).",
        "The members appointed to this committee are A. L. M. Ataullah, Chandima Veerakkodi, Premalal Jayasekara, V. Radhakrishnan, Specialist Dr. Sudarshini Fernandopulle, J. C. Alavathuwala, Nimal Lanza, Piyal Nishantha de Silva, Jayantha Katagoda, Charles Nirmalanathan, Jagath Kumara Sumitraarachi, Kings Nelson, Mudita Prishanthi, and Marjan Faleel.",
        "This committee has been appointed by the Parliamentary Select Committee headed by Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena.",
        "It is the responsibility of the House Committee to make decisions regarding various activities of the Parliament including food supply."
      ],
